    <MESSAGE value="Introduce `email` crate with IMAP/SMTP utilities and configuration support&#10;&#10;- Add `email` crate to provide generic email configuration, connection testing, email parsing, and send/fetch operations using IMAP and SMTP. &#10;- Implement `EmailConfig`, `SmtpConfig`, and `ImapConfig` for managing email settings with camelCase serialization support.&#10;- Introduce utility functions for testing email credentials, sending emails, and parsing raw RFC-822 messages.&#10;- Include comprehensive tests to validate email configuration parsing, roundtrip serialization, and connectivity." />
    <MESSAGE value="Add email connectivity module and extend permission merging logic&#10;&#10;- Introduced a new `crates/email` module for handling SMTP/IMAP connectivity, configuration, and testing. Includes `test_email_settings`, `send_email`, and `fetch_inbox` methods for email operations.&#10;- Extended the PermissionEngine to merge `docperm`, `__kiff_docperm`, and `custom_docperm` permissions with precedence, ensuring runtime permissions respect user configuration and seeded defaults.&#10;- Created tables for `docperm` and `custom_docperm` to align with extended merging behavior.&#10;- Updated `.idea` project files to reflect new module additions." />
